<h1>ABC India Web Application</h1></br>
<h2>This is a simple single-page web application that simulates a basic website for "ABC India" with navigation, user authentication, and a dashboard.<h2></br>

<h3>Features</h3>
<h4>Pages: Home, About Us, Contact Us, Login, and Sign Up.</br>
User Authentication: Users can sign up, log in, access a dashboard, and log out.</br>
Dashboard: Provides a welcome message and navigation links for logged-in users.</br>
Data Storage: Uses localStorage for storing and retrieving user data.</h4></br>

<h3>Technologies Used</h3></br>
<h4>HTML for structure.</br>
CSS for styling.</br>
JavaScript for functionality and localStorage management.</h4></br>

<h3>How It Works</h3></br>
<h4>Navigation: Links show specific sections using JavaScript.</br>
Sign Up/Login: User data is stored in localStorage. Sign-up creates a new account; login checks credentials.</br>
Dashboard: Shows after login, with options to change password (non-functional) and log out.</h4></br>

<h3>How to Run</h3></br>
<h4>Download or clone the repository.</br>
Open the HTML file in a web browser.</br>
Navigate through links and test sign-up and login features.</h4></br>

</body>
